g.text: Kim Kitsuragi: You see the lieutenant's familiar shape in the orange jacket. It turns double -- then triple -- from the pain.
You: "This is the end and I am its trumpeter, Kim. The quicker we get it done the better."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Uhuh," he nods. "I see the drouamine is working."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No need, officer. You wanted things to go South outside -- that's okay, we all do from time to time. They haven't, though. Yet."
"No need to take it back, lieutenant-yefreitor. You wanted things to go South outside -- that's okay, we all do from time to time. They haven't, though. Yet."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Maybe they are simply taking their time and will attack soon? I don't know."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I called your station after the fight. The injury was logged in. They told me they've sent officers to join you on the site."
Savoir Faire: Your balance is *way* off. You feel like you're about to fall over on that thing...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know..." He rubs his neck. "That's been there for years."
You: (Yank it out and show the dried flower, while it falls to pieces.) "This one, remember?"
You: "That's right. Let's give up. Time to start drinking."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't think so." There's a short pause. "Are you ready to limp?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. Joyce Messier. On the boat, you know? She could have helped us. It's clear the mercenaries were working for Wild Pines. At least partially..." He looks out the window.
Pain Threshold: Also, it's just close enough to endure the walk.
You: "The tie made me do it."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant does not answer, instead searching his coat pockets for something.
You: "I did all I could there."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I know you did. It's all right."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes," he replies. "The joke wasn't funny any more. I took it off."
Logic: The close proximity of death must have made the lieutenant contemplate his life choices. He's *done* with the jacket.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh yes," he nods. "She left 20 minutes prior to the tribunal showing up. I asked Mr. Garte."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Turns out it was a bad idea not to arrest her, but..." He shrugs. "Maybe it was a *good deed* that will pay off in heaven."
Logic: The lieutenant did mention doing more ballistics...
You: "They don't care about me at all."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Three: Glen, Theo, Angus. The fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause. "And Theo -- he was just too old for combat."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Four: Glen, Theo, Shanky, and Angus. The fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause.
Half Light: You're a real killer, Harry.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's face it, officer -- and this is both of our fault..." he says calmly -- without accusation. "It could have gone *a little* better. Six people are dead."
"Let's face it, officer -- and this is both of our fault..." he says calmly -- without accusation. "It could have gone *a little* better. Seven people are dead."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's part of a detective's task chain. You can do it too."
Interfacing: Actually, you *can*. You can even remove a fractured bullet, it seems...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm sure they're worried about you."
Rhetoric: No. They would be here if they were truly worried.
Drama: He may have some idea -- but he's not gonna get into it with you.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Your disco days should have been done quite a while back, officer."
"Your *disco days* should've been *done* quite a while back, lieutenant-yefreitor."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant doesn't reply -- just looks at you teetering on your feet.
Physical Instrument: He thinks you should sit back down. Back straight, now... you're not sitting ANYWHERE.
You: "Who did it then, Kim? Who killed the hanged man?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. I think your *incredibly dangerous* theory on Titus Hardie was wrong. More than six people saw Titus downstairs that night."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. I think the theory you presented -- it's someone else, outside our circle of suspects -- was right. It'd better be. Everyone within the circle is either dead or gone."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. I think the *dangerous* theory you presented on Klaasje was wrong. We have not found a motive, or a weapon for her."
"I don't know. I think the *dangerous* theory you presented on Klaasje -- or whatever her name is -- was wrong. We have not found a motive, or a weapon for her."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. I think the theory you presented -- it being Ruby -- did not add up. If we ever find her, we can pursue her on many offences, but not this one."
"I don't know. I think the theory you presented -- on Ruby -- does not add up. If she wasn't on her way to the morgue we could pursue her on many offences -- but not this one."
Kim Kitsuragi: "That was our job to find out, wasn't it? Honestly, I just don't know. Our circle of suspects is dead and gone. It's not a circle at all. It's a ruin."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. I think your *incredibly dangerous* theory about *you* being the killer was incorrect, however. There is not one piece of evidence to support it."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Honestly I think our investigation has not produced a single credible suspect." His voice is calm, matter-of-factly.
You: "They were on the roof. I did not... I did not catch them. Fucking butterfingers..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Every piece of garbage in the city is not connected to the case. You don't have to catch *everything*."
You: "No, Kim. Every piece of garbage in this city *is* connected to the case."
You: "I can't believe they're fucking useless!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "No need to be melodramatic."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Not very." He rubs his chin. "I have a concussion from the major beating me with the butt of his gun. I try to not move too much."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Not very." He rubs his chin. "I have a concussion from that woman beating me with the butt of her gun... I try to not move too much."
Rhetoric: By the way, the lieutenant does not actually believe you will be spiritually reimbursed for letting her escape. You just have to live with it.
Jump to: [You: ""Who did it then, Kim? Who killed t..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: "The gates of the harbour are boarded up. The streets are a little more empty. Apocalyptic violence is yet to erupt, I am relieved to say." He looks out the window.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Two days. In and out -- you've been up enough to take drouamine and curse. And drink water."
Rhetoric: Rhetorical flare. He does not actually welcome the return of the whores.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You're an officer of the RCM." He continues without waiting for a reply...

Kim Kitsuragi: "Titus, Fat Angus, and Theo charged. Angus and Theo did not make it. They both died before they made it to intensive care. Titus survives. So do Alain and the musician, I forget his name..."

"Titus, Fat Angus, and Theo charged. Angus and Theo died before they made it to intensive care, Titus died in the hospital. Yesterday. Alain and the young musician, I forget his name... They're all that's left."
Kim Kitsuragi: "And Elizabeth too -- Elizabeth Beaufort was her name. The gardener."
You: "The tie made me do it."
Kim Kitsuragi: He does not answer, and searches for something in his coat pocket instead.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happened? We tried to take the diplomatic route and hoped they wouldn't attack first. They did. The major gave the command."
Endurance: Through tears and blood and stitches tearing it *should* be possible.
You: "Has anyone from my station been to see me?"
You: "There's still a... 28% possibility the shot came from a distance."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should go upstairs, rethink the ballistics *in situ*." A light nod, through some pain. "I agree with this. What else?"
Kim Kitsuragi: He arches his brow -- the ceiling fan patiently spins overhead.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's do that." He extinguishes the cigarette on the sole of his boot.
"Let's do that. We can start upstairs in Klaasje's bedroom -- with your ballistics idea." He extinguishes his cigarette on the sole of his boot.
"Let's do that. We can start upstairs in Klaasje's bedroom -- I have not done a thorough sweep after she left." He extinguishes his cigarette on the sole of his boot.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's do that." He looks to the ceiling. Then the door. "Actually, I'm too tired to walk. Klaasje's room is nearby."
"Let's do that. We can start upstairs in Klaasje's bedroom -- the ballistics idea..." He sighs.
"Let's do that. We can start upstairs in Klaasje's bedroom -- I have not done a thorough sweep after she left..." He sighs.

Esprit de Corps: A man and a woman sit in the front seat of an armoured motor carriage. The woman is driving, the man lights a cigarette. Jean Vicquemare is his name, the asphalt vanishes under the wheels of the machine. Ahead, harbour cranes rise to the sky...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Sunrise, Parabellum. Sunrise, Prepare-for-War. It's an old revolutionary saying."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I think we may have held it off -- for now." He unzips his bomber jacket. "Barely."
You: "I seriously want this... social order to collapse now."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I see the drouamine is working."
You: "I warned them I am a killer of killers..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I shot and wounded him. While Glen took a bullet in the spine. It was meant for me -- he did not survive." There's a pause.
Rhetoric: He did not expect you both to survive once you stepped between those two armies.
Endurance: His smoking, his hunched back... you have it worse, but he took a real beating. That cigarette has *medicinal* purposes.
Hand/Eye Coordination: He sounds a *tiny bit* sorry he did not find it before you got hit.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happened? You shot the major. Unsuccessfully. A firefight ensued."
"What happened? You shot the colonel -- unsuccessfully. Then you threw your gun at him. A firefight ensued."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We won't get to him anymore. The good news is -- he's not coming here either. I did some damage."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's face it, officer..." he says calmly -- without accusation. "It could have gone a little better. You could've *not* missed with the bomb. If you already threw it."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The bruising in your shoulder is negligible. The armour took the brunt of the fire."
Savoir Faire: You won't be able to dance much, that's for sure. You should be able to live with limping around though.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good. You'll need to be... whatever that is."
You: "If they're so worried about me where are they?"
You: Better not agitate yourself further, it already hurts.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We can't talk to Evrart, the harbour is in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. And Joyce has left too."
"We can't talk to Evrart, the harbour is in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. Joyce has left too, thanks to our meddling."
"We can't talk to Evrart, the harbour is in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. Joyce has left too, we never got to know what she would have told us. I'm sure it was important."
"We can't talk to Evrart, the harbour is in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. We never even met the Wild Pines representative, and she's gone too..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No." There's a short pause. "Are you ready to limp?"
Pain Threshold: That concussion must be making him dizzy.
You: "It's not *whether* I am -- I am. Jules told me so, he's from my station."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay," he concedes -- clearly not meaning it.
Kim Kitsuragi: There's a little pause -- he says nothing as well.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Something," he repeats. It does not sound like he's enthused about this *some-thing*.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hmh..." He hums -- thinking about something else.
Reaction Speed: Isn't that written on your...
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's not *ouch* time yet. You just got a *drouamine* pill an hour ago. Wait until it wears off."
Encyclopedia: Drouamine. Then it's not *that* bad. Neither surgical, nor organ-damage bad. But still under-the-counter bad.
Kim Kitsuragi: "The whores, yes. That's good to hear."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I killed her." The lieutenant takes a cigarette from his coat pocket and lights it. A bitter smell fills the room. "And that's what happened."

"I was not able to kill him -- as I should have. Krenel took him..." The lieutenant takes a cigarette from his coat pocket and lights it. A bitter smell fills the room. "A stray bullet killed de Paule, though. And that's what happened."
You: "And they're all dead, all three... of the contractors?"
"And they're dead... the rest of the mercenaries?"
You: "I thought you only smoked one a day."
You: "How many casualties... on the Union's side? Total?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "No. She bled out before Evrart's surgeon could help her. Evrart sent his personal doctor but..." He shakes his head. "A costly loss for the Union. She was being trained for leadership."
You: "It's a total shit show, Kim."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, officer," he says calmly. "Six people are dead. It's not a success."
"Yes, officer," he says calmly. "Seven people are dead. It's not a success."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You tried to throw an improvised petroleum bomb. It missed. Then you said *it's a fiasco, bratan* in a funny voice. A firefight ensued."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Pretty bad, officer. You've suffered two wounds. The first is below your shoulder. The bullet passed through your shoulder blade, luckily missing your lung -- and heart."
Volition: If it's possible, then by pure willpower alone. You are going to have to become... a psycholocomotor.
Kim Kitsuragi: There's a pause. "I'm sure they're worried about you."
Rhetoric: That means he hasn't seen them around while you were out. They're not *really* worried about you. If they were, wouldn't they be here?
You: "It's simple, we have to locate *communism*. Communism killed him."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm afraid we may not be able to locate communism, detective -- on account of it being dead."
You: "The fucking *May bells*, Kim, the flowers."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Really? Because, to me, it seems solving crimes is *hard*."
Esprit de Corps: That's between you and them, he thinks.
Interfacing: Can you? You're pretty sure you can't.
Esprit de Corps: "Back to that shithole," he says.
Empathy: This is not the first person to die in his place. He goes on.
You: "I don't see how it could have gone any better."
Kim Kitsuragi: "As retaliation, their rifleman shot you. He hit. With his carabine -- I was looking for a clear line of sight. When I found it..."
You: "If not my station, then who treated me?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Easy now..." The lieutenant turns double again, before your eyes. An orange hue of pain...
You: "I'm very bad, Kim. Things are very bad."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks at you -- teetering on your feet.
Jump to: [Physical Instrument: "He thinks you should sit back down...."]
Kim Kitsuragi: "*Sunrise, parabellum*," the lieutenant says. He's in the middle of a freshly cleaned room, with the fan above his head like a halo. His face is covered in bruises.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Don't be narcissistic. Half the cops in Revachol West are his *peones*. Even if you are, it is not a decisive factor in this case."
You: "There are all these... old bunkers and weapon caches around..."
"There are all these... old bunkers and weapon caches. Revolutionary era!"
"There was that... hidden bunker under the boardwalk. Revolutionary era!"
"There was that... hidden weapons cache under the building. Revolutionary era!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "We could find thousands more if we wanted. All of Revachol is full of them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm ready to hear what you think about solving crimes now."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It can feel that way sometimes, yes."
You: "Are you sure? I see communism *everywhere*, telling us what to think, stifling... ouch, my *leg hurts*!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Ideology does not have anything to do with the murder investigation at hand, I'm sorry -- it does not."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I am glad that you do."
You: "If I would have presented the theory better... to their leader..."
Shivers: A gust of wind blows in from the bay, the duraluminium box around you vibrates imperceptibly... a familiar cold, a red thread on the roof upstairs. Taut. Plucked like a string by the gust.
You: "My gun. It's engraved on it."
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happened? You shot the major in the face. A firefight ensued."
Kim Kitsuragi: "As retaliation, their rifleman tried shooting you. He hit the cuirass... I heard it go off. I was looking for a clear line of sight to him."
You: "An antique bullet... from a Belle-Magrave, 4.46 mm. How hard can it be to find one? How hard can it *be*?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's extremely easy. There are thousands lying around from the war. All completely unusable. It's precisely how *easy* it is that makes that bullet useless."
"It's *extremely* easy. There are thousands lying around, *we* found one. All completely unusable. It's precisely how easy it is to find one that makes the bullet useless."
Drama: He is definitely not on La Puta Madre's take.
You: "Communism is making a *massive* comeback, Kim."
You: "Good. It's good it's dead. Communism is *stupid*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Maybe it's her? Maybe she kept her end... Either way, Ruby's gone. And Klaasje -- well, at least *she's* safely locked away."
"It's a little late to elicit her support now. Ruby's gone. And Klaasje -- well, at least she's safely locked away."
You: "You think she could.... be of more use to us?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why not..." He extinguishes the cigarette on the sole of his boot.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why not?" He looks to the ceiling, then to the door.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Another look at the window perhaps -- the one he was shot through? I don't know... I can't think of anything better."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Four: Glen, Theo, Angus, the fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Five: Glen, Theo, Shanky, and Angus, the fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. We have also completely failed. But that's okay."
You: "You misunderstand me. (cough) I meant that in a... *disco* way."
Kim Kitsuragi: "De Paule was the last to die." He nods. "Evrart had their bodies returned to Krenel for a funeral. The company is yet to retaliate."
He nods. "Evrart had their bodies returned to Krenel for a funeral. The company is yet to retaliate."
You: "Odd. You haven't seen any, have you?"
You: "Okay. Yes. I can see how it's hard to indict someone who is not actually a person."
Esprit de Corps: A man of his word, this killer of killers.
Esprit de Corps: Thank you. Although...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Locked up? No, she would be of more *use* to us free, honestly. But it was the right thing to do."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Five: Glen, Theo, Angus. The fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause. "And Titus."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Reasonably bad. You were shot in the left quadriceps -- that's your thigh. It appears no major arteries were nicked. The bullet was removed and a bacterial infection treated with mercurochrome."

Kim Kitsuragi: "The second shot hit you in the thigh -- the left quadriceps." He points to your leg. "No major arteries were nicked, but the bullet had to be removed. A bacterial infection was treated with mercurochrome."
Inland Empire: But they seemed so mysterious.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Are you ready to limp?"
You: "You don't think it was a good idea?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know what to think. It might not have been a *bad* idea. There is a *pin* somewhere in the machine. Something is keeping Krenel from sending in a death squad..." He looks out the window.
You: "We should check Klaasje's room, upstairs."
"We should check Mrs. Katarzine Alasije's room, upstairs."
"We should check Miss Oranje Disco Dancer's room, upstairs."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Neither do I. Let's walk and hope something happens, before you bleed to death. Klaasje's room is nearby..." He looks to the door.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Garte confirmed she left 20 minutes prior to the tribunal showing up."
Kim Kitsuragi: "But what's done is done. The violence is cordoned off, the mercenary tribunal is neutralized. The worst scenario has not materialized -- yet."
"But what's done is done. The violence is cordoned off, the hornets did not get into the beehive." He rubs his swollen chin. "The worst scenario has not materialized -- yet."
Volition: See? There's that. You can do ballistics!
Kim Kitsuragi: "As retaliation, their rifleman tried shooting you. He missed -- or you dodged..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Because we *deterred* them? Or Joyce did? Maybe the harbour -- in full lockdown -- is too costly a target. Or maybe..." he breathes in the fumes, thinking.
You: "What about the hole in the... ouch... wall? Someone was checking her out."
You: "The miracle hasn't happened yet. It's not over yet."
You: "You know what I think about... solving crimes?" (Conclude.)
You: "Okay, so once more -- Klaasje has *escaped*?"
You: "Something is creeping around out there. I sense it."
You: "This is because I'm a La Puta Madre's peone, isn't it?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Five: Glen, Theo, Shanky, Angus. The fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause. "And Titus."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Then I shot and wounded him while Glen took a bullet in the spine." He nods. "It was meant for me. Glen did not survive." There's a pause.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's face it, officer," he says calmly -- without accusation. "It could have gone a little better. You could've *not* missed."
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""But what's done is done. The viole..."]

Kim Kitsuragi: "Reasonably bad. You were shot in the left quadriceps -- that's your thigh. The outer side thankfully, no major arteries were nicked. The bullet was removed and a bacterial infection treated with mercurochrome."
Pain Threshold: It's nothing. You're alive, that's what matters.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I killed her," the lieutenant repeats himself. "And that's what happened."
"I was not able to kill him -- as I should have. Krenel took him..." the lieutenant states again. "A stray bullet killed de Paule, though. And that's what happened."
You: "Pity all the whores and traitors haven't been washed away! It's like I suffer... (cough) but for what?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. He's still alive too."
Half Light: There is unveiled anger in his voice.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Four: Glen, Theo, Angus. The fat one, he... took a lot of bullets." There's a pause. "And Titus."
You: "I didn't know you could... do that."
Kim Kitsuragi: He does not know what to reply. Looks out of the window, then back at you.
Kim Kitsuragi: "That you did." The lieutenant looks at you with a peculiar expression. He then continues...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Mr. Garte cleaned it. It took him an entire day."
You: "How long have I been out?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You were bleeding out by then..." He thinks. "You warned me -- I was able to disarm Kortenaer before he got the jump on me."
"You were bleeding out. I think you said something about your wife... And you *warned* me. I was able to disarm the major before he got the jump on me."
"You were bleeding out. I think you said no one wants to party with you. And you *warned* me. I was able to disarm the major before he got the jump on me."
"You were bleeding out. I think you said you lied about being an amnesiac. And you *warned* me. I was able to disarm the major before he got the jump on me."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You were bleeding out, you said something, I don't know what..." He thinks. "And you warned me. I was able to disarm officer de Paule before she got the jump on me."
"You were bleeding out by then. I think you said something about your wife. And you warned me. I was able to disarm one of them, de Paule, before she got the jump on me."
"You were bleeding out by then. I think you said that no one wants to party with you. And you warned me. I was able to disarm one of them, de Paule, before she got the jump on me."
"You were bleeding out by then. I think you said you lied about being an amnesiac. And you warned me. I was able to disarm one of them, de Paule, before she got the jump on me."
Kim Kitsuragi: "... is in a private hospital across the river. Krenel claimed him from the local butcher shop, where Titus died. Turns out he's *insured*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "And..." he smiles: "We are still alive -- both of us."
Endurance: With considerable pain and the stitches tearing every now and then -- you should be able to do it.
You: "Actually, I want to talk about this crime some more, before I tell you what I think about its hardness."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Neither do I. Let's walk and hope something happens before you bleed to death. Klaasje's room is nearby..." He extinguishes the cigarette on the sole of his boot.
You: "The piss-jacket, Kim... you took it off?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh no, officer," he says calmly -- without accusation. "It's pretty bad. Six people are dead."
"Oh no, officer," he says calmly -- without accusation. "It's pretty bad. Seven people are dead."
"Oh no, Harry," he says calmly -- without accusation. "It's pretty bad. Seven people are dead."
Pain Threshold: You can take it. Just don't lean on that leg of yours too heavily.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, she left yesterday morning. To meet the board of Wild Pines -- or that is what I've heard. There's a *pin* somewhere in the machine that keeps Krenel from sending in a death squad..." He looks out the window.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good." There's a pause. "Where do you want to limp to?"
You: "Let's just aimlessly wander until a clue presents itself."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Absolutely," he nods. "There's no other way to go about it. We screwed up."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's face it, officer..." he says calmly -- without accusation. "It could have gone a little better. The diplomatic approach was terrible. It was my mistake. I should have attacked..."
"Let's face it, officer..." he says calmly -- without accusation. "It could have gone a little better. You could have been *armed*. It was my mistake too, I should have attacked..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Maybe it's her? Maybe she kept her end. Either way, Ruby's gone. And Klaasje too. We really should have arrested her, you know."
"It's a little late to elicit her support now. Ruby's gone. And Klaasje too. We really should have arrested her, you know."
Kim Kitsuragi: "She never had a chance. She should not have been there in the first place. There was no way to *convince* them."
Volition: Stop this line of thought now. You're too broken for ghosts.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happened? You threw an improvised petroleum bomb at the major. A firefight ensued."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Things would be worse if you didn't warn me." There's a pause. "Thank you. I did not see her coming. Stupid of me..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Things would be much worse if you didn't warn me." There's a pause. "Thank you. I did not see him coming. Stupid of me..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Do you? Because we can't talk to Evrart, the harbour is in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. And Joyce has left too."
"Do you? Because we can't talk to Evrart, the harbour's in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. Joyce has left too, thanks to our meddling."
"Do you? Because we can't talk to Evrart, the harbour's in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. Joyce has left too; we never got to know what she would have told us."
"Do you? Because we can't talk to Evrart, the harbour's in lockdown -- everyone in there is outside our grasp now. The Wild Pines representative has left too, and we never even met her..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes." He pulls on his cigarette intently.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes." He says. "God curse the footprints -- not solving the case for us. *Au diable*."
You: "You're not ready to give up, are you?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Every piece of garbage in the city is not connected to the case. You don't have to keep *everything*."
Perception (Sight): It's morning outside, you think.
Visual Calculus: Ballistics. In Klaasje's room. Do it *properly*.
